Center: Center of Nuclear Physics Data, Russian Federal Nuclear Center (VNIIEF), Sarov, Russia
title: Investigation of the reaction S-32(d,p)S-33 in the deuteron energy range 1.5-2.5 MeV.

x4freetext: Investigation of the reaction S-32(d,p)S-33 in the
A semi-conductor spectrometer consisting of an
ORTEC-type detector made of n-silicon was used.
in opposite directions were placed in the reaction
plane inside the chamber. One of the detectors was
usually placed at 135 degr. and used as a monitor, the
other was rotated from 15 to 160 degr.
The Ag2S layer evaporated on a thin silver backing was
used as a target. The target thicknesses for 2 MeV
deuteron energy were of the order of 20 keV.
